<p>
<seg id=1> International Supervisors in Kosovo said it was still hopeful to resume cease-fire there, although the battle arose between the Sebian Security Troops and the Albania separatists for days. </seg>
<seg id=2> Pulis, Spokesman for the International Supervisors, said on Monday that the situation in Kosovo, Yugoslavia remained calm. </seg>
<seg id=3> At least 12 died in the battle last week. </seg>
<seg id=4> Garmac, Chairman of the OSCE, blamed the two sides in battle to revoke the violence. </seg>
